analysisPopulations.name: Screened Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Screened Set includes all participants who signed an informed consent form (ICF).
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Screened Set includes all participants who signed an informed consent form (ICF).

analysisPopulations.name: Enrolled Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Enrolled Set includes all participants who signed an ICF and were enrolled in the study.
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Enrolled Set includes all participants who signed an ICF and were enrolled in the study.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Signed ICF AND enrolled in the study

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis (FA) Set includes all participants who were enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug. The FA Set will be used for all efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.label: FA
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis (FA) Set includes all participants who were enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug. The FA Set will be used for all efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled AND received >=1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Per Protocol (PP) Set includes all participants in the FA Set who do not have any major protocol deviations that would impact the interpretability of the efficacy data. The PP Set will be used for sensitivity analyses of the primary efficacy endpoint. Major protocol deviations will be identified and documented before database lock.
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Per Protocol (PP) Set includes all participants in the FA Set who do not have any major protocol deviations that would impact the interpretability of the efficacy data. The PP Set will be used for sensitivity analyses of the primary efficacy endpoint. Major protocol deviations will be identified and documented before database lock.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of FA Set AND no major protocol deviations impacting efficacy

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Set includes all participants who received at least 1 dose of study drug. The Safety Set will be used for all safety analyses.
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Set includes all participants who received at least 1 dose of study drug. The Safety Set will be used for all safety analyses.

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Pharmacokinetic (PK) Analysis Set includes all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient plasma concentration data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PK parameter. The PK Analysis Set will be used for all PK analyses.
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Pharmacokinetic (PK) Analysis Set includes all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient plasma concentration data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PK parameter. The PK Analysis Set will be used for all PK analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of Safety Set AND has sufficient data for >=1 PK parameter

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacodynamic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Pharmacodynamic (PD) Analysis Set includes all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient PD data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PD parameter. The PD Analysis Set will be used for all PD analyses.
analysisPopulations.label: PD
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Pharmacodynamic (PD) Analysis Set includes all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient PD data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PD parameter. The PD Analysis Set will be used for all PD analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of Safety Set AND has sufficient data for >=1 PD parameter
